THE LEGAL NOTES
We're UNUM, Inc. (or collectively "The Company"), a proud LA-native founded, California Company headquartered in sunny Los Angeles (come say hi if you're ever out in LA! We'd also love to share with you our go-to restaurants, bars, and spots in the city!).
When you storytell with us (or access our services, apps, and website (our Platform)), these terms apply. They are important for the both of us as they set out "what we expect from each other and they also give you helpful info. You can always find out more through our Members Care Team and Care Center — we love hearing from you, we're family, remember!?
We keep these terms updated and may add to or edit them every so often, so remember to circle back before you continue using our Platform as the latest version will apply.
ABOUT YOU
To storytell with us, you need to:
Be at least 13 years old to use the Platform;
Have an UNUM account to access most features and functionality of the Platform;
Have a credit or debit card that we accept (see our Care Center for details of current payment providers) or be able to make mobile subscription or in-app purchases, in which case the fee is collected via Apple (for iOS) and Google (for Android) (our Billing Service Providers; and
Be authorized to use that payment method (e.g. it is in your name or you have permission to use it).
UNUM ACCOUNT
Your UNUM account gives you access to the services and functionality that we may establish and maintain from time to time and in our sole discretion. We may maintain different types of accounts for different types of Members (to make your UNUM experience aligned with you and and your story). If you open an account on behalf of a company, organization, or other entity, then (a) you "includes you and that entity, and (b) you represent and warrant that you are an authorized representative of the entity with the authority to bind the entity to this Agreement, and that you agree to this Agreement on the entity's behalf. By connecting to UNUM with a third-party service, you give us permission to access and use your information from that service as permitted by that service, and to store necessary credentials for that service (so we can provide the expected experience for you in UNUM).
You may never use another User's account without permission (no one likes double dipping). We're excited that you want to use UNUM (who wouldn't), but you need to create your own account so we can make sure you have a perfect and customly catered experience that you expect (and deserve!). When creating your account, you must provide accurate and complete information (otherwise, how are we supposed to perform our contract with you!). You are solely responsible for the activity that occurs on your account, and you must keep your account password secure. Helpful tip: We encourage you to use "strong" passwords (passwords that use a combination of upper and lower case letters, numbers and symbols) with your account. You must notify UNUM immediately of any breach of security or unauthorized use of your account. UNUM will not be liable for any losses caused by any unauthorized use of your account.
You may control your Member's profile and how you interact with the Platform by changing the settings in your Account settings page. By providing UNUM your email address you consent to our using the email address to send you Platform-related notices, including any notices required by law, in lieu of communication by postal mail (we are a paperless forward company). We may also use your email address to send you other messages, such as changes to features of the Platform and special offers. If you do not want to receive such email messages, you may opt out or change your preferences in your Account settings page. Opting out may prevent you from receiving email messages regarding updates, improvements, or offers (and may leave you in a deep FOMO state, we wouldn't wish that on our worst enemy!).
We may make changes to the Platform, services, and features at anytime (that is the nature of software-based businesses and a real benefit for you and us! It means we can release more features, faster, and improve our overall service and Platform for you - queue the house party!). We may be able to create usage limits for the Platform. We may permanently or temporarily terminate or suspend your access to the Platform (including the right to cancel any hosted sites) without notice and liability for any reason. If that is ever the case (which we hope will never happen!) you will be bound to this Agreement.
