THINGS YOU SHOULDN’T DO
We know it is obvious, but you must not misuse, alter, or tamper with our websites, apps, or other services ("Platform") (e.g. hack, introduce viruses, trojans, worms, reverse engineer, decompile, disassemble, decipher any portion of our Platform) or otherwise pollute our tech or functionality or steal our Members' data. Doing any of these things or similarly related activities may be a criminal offence (who wins in this scenario? Instead, together let's do good and make this world a better place -- one story at a time. Leave a positive impact on life, not a negative one!). Doing any of those malicious activities also gets in the way of giving our loyal UNUM members and community the best possible service, so we take any actions against them very seriously. UNUM will report any such breach or activity (and all the information about the people carrying it out) to the relevant law enforcement authorities.
Like eating healthy, working out, and taking your vitamins -- we recommend you use virus protection software when using any Platform, including ours. Although our team works hard to stop people messing with our Platform, we can't guarantee that it will always be secure from bugs, viruses, or trouble-makers.
Another point, you're not allowed to use automated systems or software to extract data from our Platform (known as ‘screen scraping'). Another way to look at it, you should not be accessing the Platform, Service or sending more requests messages to the UNUM servers than a person can reasonably produce in the same period of time.
